    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, i guess. i'm just worried about the whole \"increased purchasing power\" argument people always use. if i have to raise my prices just to cover wages, won't my customers just stop coming? does that argument about workers spending more actually hold up for a small shop like mine, or is it mostly just theory?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The increased purchasing power argument suggests that workers will spend their higher wages in the local economy, benefitting the business. However, studies have shown that the phenomenon is often called the \" millionaire's myth,\" as most workers, even low-income individuals, tend to spend their entire paycheck or save it, rather than allocating excess funds to local businesses. For truly low-income workers, a higher wage may barely cover living expenses, and thus won't have the desired trickle-down effect on the business.",
      "source": "target",
